<br>
there's really no reason to make anything more complicated than need be.<br>
<br>
Up to now, the NToV rotation was all mobs past the Door.<br>
<br>
I can't really see any reason for that to change, or more rules put into place, or &quot;watchdogs&quot; assigned to make sure that all the rules are being adhered to.<br>
<br>
Any guild that can get up a Raid force to successfully get to Iki and Eashan can probably take down Aary, and be part of the NToV rotation.<br>
<br>
It all comes down to courtesy.  There is a NToV rotation, which is all mobs past the Door.  Because of the way VI wanted timers on each individual mob in a zone, NToV can spawn weirdly.  Up to now, all Rotation Guilds waited until Full Spawn before going in.  Up to now, a guild got onto the Rotation by killing Aary, which has, up to now, included Iki and Eashan.  There doesn't seem to be any reason to change things *at this time*.<br>
<br>
That is not to say things can't change in the future.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkoak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DarkOak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Blade</span><br>  Posts: 451<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/18/02 1:18:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ntov</span><hr size=1> All I can say is.. if you don't have some damn good monks.. good luck with the rampage drakes/wyverns. Heh.<br>
